  "title" : "How annotation internally works in java",
  "body" : "<p>I know how to create custom annotation. But i am unable to understand how does it work internally. If i take example of spring annontation. </p>\n\n<pre><code>@PropertySource(value = { \"classpath:database.properties\" }). \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>if we see internal details of @PropertySource annotation</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Target({ java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE })\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Documented\n@Repeatable(PropertySources.class)\npublic @interface PropertySource {\n    public abstract String name();\n\n    public abstract String[] value();\n\n    public abstract boolean ignoreResourceNotFound();\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>We do not have provided any implementation here for loading property file.\nThen How is it loading property file from classpath. Who is working behind the scene ?</p>\n"
